	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />There's an animation book by Preston Blair usually called "Animation" that's readily available that teaches a good cartoony style.  You can get it free online <a href="http://www.animationarchive.org/2006/05/media-preston-blairs-animation-first.html" class="postlink">here</a>  if you can't find a local copy.
<br />
<br />Also, the dude who made Ren &amp; Stimpy has online lessons at his <a href="http://johnkcurriculum.blogspot.com/" class="postlink">blog</a>.
<br />
<br />The egg face part of the book is really handy, plus you can use the egg face to practice shading, which I strongly recommend.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


