	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Believe it or not, I really think that tracing images is a great way to learn how to draw. I think that's where I got a lot of my drawing ability from when I was really young.
<br />
<br />I've never really learned a lot from instructional books; most of it just comes from practice, and a real desire to draw or paint. I picked painting up immediately simply because I wanted to do it. It also helps if you know an artist who you can ask to comment on your work. My sister is one of the best artists I know, and I show her my work a lot of the time to get her feedback. It really helps in the long run when all of those little tips and pointers you get add up.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
